<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="97194de0-c722-5c20-81d3-133e2e2b5ca2" activityNameId="3275f5fa-364e-4974-8020-5871cbdfb5eb" parentActivityId="c98cd03d-6ca2-47cb-a161-44e877bcc6ef" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">bamboo pole production</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">From reception of bamboo culm and treatment products at processing facility</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This activity ends with Bamboo Pole (u=20%) at the processing facility. The dataset includes the inputs drying, treatment, trimming processes, as far as they are available. The dataset includes infrastructure. Losses of boric acid to the environment are not included in the dataset. However, they are not expected to be significant.
</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset is a weighted average of the existing local datasets (BR, CN, CO, PH). It represents the production of 1 Kg of bamboo pole. Bamboo culm with a water content of u =80 % is used for the production of bamboo pole. The production takes place at a bamboo processing facility and includes technical drying to a final water content of u =20% and trimming of culms. The figures origin from mainly calculations and literature values.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">The pole is derived directly from the bamboo culm and is usually trimmed to between 4 and 6 m and treated against fungi and pests using boric acid. Bamboo poles can be used directly for the construction of columns, beams, or struts and are also the main input for other bamboo-based construction materials (BBCM) (Vogtländer et al., 2010, Vogtländer et al., 2014).  This dataset was developed with the support of the International Organization for Bamboo and Rattan INBAR</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">Ref:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">Vogtländer, J., P. van der Lugt, and H. Brezet, The sustainability of bamboo products for local and Western European applications. LCAs and land-use. Journal of Cleaner Production, 2010. 18(13): p. 1260-1269.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4"></text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="5">Vogtländer, J.G., N.M. van der Velden, and P. van der Lugt, Carbon sequestration in LCA, a proposal for a new approach based on the global carbon cycle; cases on wood and on bamboo. Int. J. Life Cycle Assess., 2014. 19(1): p. 13-23.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="627be0b2-04e5-4179-b1eb-98755b9dda04">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">162:Manufacture of products of wood, cork, straw and plaiting materials</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="7846b897-7c04-4f9f-b607-2b83fcd9a74c">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">RoW</shortname>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Current production technology</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2010-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true"/>
